Agentic Travel Planning System
Overview
The Collaborative Travel Planning Platform is a web-based system designed to help
individuals and groups organize trips more efficiently. It provides a structured space
where users can collect destinations, plan activities, manage accommodations and
transportation, and coordinate with travel partners. Since group trips often involve
different preferences, schedules, and budgets, the platform helps balance these
constraints and create itineraries that work for everyone. By integrating an Agentic
AI component, the system can also assist users by generating travel plans,
suggesting activities, and dynamically adjusting itineraries based on user
preferences, time, and budget.
Objectives
1. Trip Workspace
Develop a system where users can create and manage travel plans.
Each trip should function as a shared workspace where users can:
● define travel dates and trip duration
● add destinations or activities
● maintain travel notes and considerations
Trips may be planned individually or collaboratively with other participants.
2. Destination Discovery and Saving
Allow users to collect and organize places they want to visit.
Users should be able to:
● save destinations, attractions, or restaurants
● organize saved places within a trip
● attach notes or preferences to saved locations
This helps travelers maintain a curated list of potential activities.
3. Itinerary Planning
Users should be able to organize destinations and activities into a structured
itinerary.
Possible capabilities include:
● arranging activities by day or time
● modifying schedules when plans change
● organizing travel routes between destinations
This helps travelers design clear and flexible travel plans.
4. Collaborative Planning
Enable multiple users to collaborate on the same trip.
Participants in a trip should be able to:
● suggest destinations or activities
● discuss and refine plans
● propose modifications to the itinerary
This allows groups to plan trips collectively.
5. Budget Awareness
The platform should allow users to estimate and track travel expenses.
Possible features include:
● defining a trip budget
● estimating costs for activities or transportation
● monitoring approximate spending across the itinerary
This helps travelers keep plans within financial constraints.
6. Agentic AI Travel Assistant
Participants should integrate an Agentic AI component that helps users plan and
refine trips.
The agent may assist with tasks such as:
● generating itinerary suggestions based on user preferences
● recommending destinations or activities within budget constraints
● adjusting itineraries when travel parameters change
● summarizing travel plans and suggesting improvements
The goal is to create an intelligent assistant that helps travelers organize trips more
efficiently.
Expected Outcome
Teams should deliver a prototype platform capable of:
● creating and managing collaborative trip plans
● collecting and organizing destinations and activities
● structuring multi-day travel itineraries
● supporting group-based planning and discussion
● assisting travelers through an Agentic AI planning assistant
